+# Regression Proof Safety Net Fixtures
+
+Fixtures in this directory protect Spring Boot migration contracts with sanitized test data only.
+
+Phase 1 intentionally adds no raw payload fixture yet. Later phases should place focused JSON or payload fixtures here only when a test compares exact serialization for amount, date, null, or Rabbit body behavior.
+
+Rules:
+
+- Do not copy real bearer tokens, JWTs, `Authorized-Party-Token` values, encrypted config values, passwords, API keys, partner credentials, private keys, production identifiers, or real customer data.
+- Keep fixtures small and tie each fixture to a test name that documents the contract it protects.
+- Preserve whitespace and field order only when exact raw serialization is the behavior under test.
